<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,303,815,841]" box="[189,303,815,841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,815,841]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,815,841]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1398,861,922]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The species has been reported from fruits of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bab." authorityName="Bab." box="[711,1025,861,888]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Cuscuta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="approximata">
<emphasis box="[711,963,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cuscuta approximata</emphasis>
Bab.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.Dumortier" authorityYear="1829" box="[1039,1189,861,887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cuscutaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cuscutaceae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry box="[1234,1349,861,887]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[189,351,896,922]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova M. D." box="[366,522,896,922]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 203" refId="ref12726" refString="Zerova M. D. 2010. Palaearctic species of the genus Eurytoma (Hymenoptera, Chalcidoidea, Eurytomidae): morphological and biological peculiarities, trophic associations and key to determination. Vestnik Zoologii Supplement 24: 1 - 203." type="journal article" year="2010">Zerova 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,962,1340]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
This species has characters of the 
<emphasis box="[593,705,962,988]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">nodularis</emphasis>
species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Lotfalizadeh H. &amp; Delvare G. &amp; Rasplus J. - Y." box="[891,1180,962,988]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="441 - 510" refId="ref11919" refString="Lotfalizadeh H., Delvare G. &amp; Rasplus J. - Y. 2007. Phylogenetic analysis of Eurytominae (Chalcidoidea: Eurytomidae) based on morphological characters. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 151: 441 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2007.00308. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Lotfalizadeh 
<emphasis box="[1049,1109,962,988]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), and with sharing conspicuous mesopleural shelf, carinate fore coxae and distinctly petiolate gaster, it is consequently transferred from 
<taxonomicName authority="Illiger, 1807" authorityName="Illiger" authorityYear="1807" box="[387,653,1032,1058]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Eurytoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[387,503,1033,1058]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Eurytoma</emphasis>
Illiger, 1807
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1904" box="[806,927,1033,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Aximopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[806,927,1033,1059]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Aximopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lotfalizadeh &amp; Karimpour &amp; Delvare &amp; Rasplus" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zerova" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[941,1199,1032,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Aximopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis box="[941,1199,1032,1059]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Aximopsis deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from closely related species by the following set of characters: head round and slightly wider than long in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[380,473,1102,1129]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Aximopsis deserticola (Zerova, 2004) comb. nov. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Fore wing venation. D. Mesosoma in lateral view. E. Head and antennae in lateral view. F. Male in lateral view. G. Male antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011140/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
); inner orbital margin coarsely punctate, and appearing to be slightly carinate; all funicular segments in female distinctly longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[933,1027,1138,1164]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Aximopsis deserticola (Zerova, 2004) comb. nov. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Fore wing venation. D. Mesosoma in lateral view. E. Head and antennae in lateral view. F. Male in lateral view. G. Male antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011140/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
), F1 about 2.5× as long as its width; fore coxa distinctly carinate in frontal view; mesopleuron with an obvious ventral shelf, carinate anteriorly and with an oblong comb anteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[823,919,1208,1234]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Aximopsis deserticola (Zerova, 2004) comb. nov. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Fore wing venation. D. Mesosoma in lateral view. E. Head and antennae in lateral view. F. Male in lateral view. G. Male antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011140/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
); marginal vein as long as postmarginal vein, slightly longer than stigmal vein, postmarginal vein about 1.5× as long as stigmal vein (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1384,1243,1269]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Aximopsis deserticola (Zerova, 2004) comb. nov. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Fore wing venation. D. Mesosoma in lateral view. E. Head and antennae in lateral view. F. Male in lateral view. G. Male antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011140/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
); metasoma of female rounded, as long as mesosoma in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[982,1076,1278,1305]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[285,1302,317,1877]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Aximopsis deserticola (Zerova, 2004) comb. nov. A. Female in lateral view. B. Head of female in frontal view. C. Fore wing venation. D. Mesosoma in lateral view. E. Head and antennae in lateral view. F. Male in lateral view. G. Male antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4011140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4011140/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
), with long petiole, slightly longer than wide.
</paragraph>
